Yaya Toure has hinted that he is open to leaving Manchester City this summer . 
  The midfielder has two years left on his contract at the Etihad Stadium . 
  Toure's agent Dimitri Seluk says he wants to meet with City to discuss his future . 
  City are prepared to listen to offers for the Ivory Coast international . 
  Inter Milan boss Roberto Mancini is interested in Toure . 
 